   123	    "§6930. Effective date (a) Preliminary notification Not later than ninety days after "
   124	    "promulgation of regulations under section 6921 of this title identifying by its "
   125	    "characteristics or listing any substance as hazardous waste subject to this subchapter, any "
   126	    "person generating or transporting such substance or owning or operating a facility for "
   127	    "treatment, storage, or disposal of such substance shall file with the Administrator (or with "
   128	    "States having authorized hazardous waste permit programs under section 6926 of this title) a "
   129	    "notification stating the location and general description of such activity and the "
   130	    "identified or listed hazardous wastes handled by such person. Not later than fifteen months "
   131	    "after November 8, 1984— (1) the owner or operator of any facility which produces a fuel (A) "
   132	    "from any hazardous waste identified or listed under section 6921 of this title, (B) from "
   133	    "such hazardous waste identified or listed under section 6921 of this title and any other "
   134	    "material, (C) from used oil, or (D) from used oil and any other material; (2) the owner or "
   135	    "operator of any facility (other than a single- or two-family residence) which burns for "
   136	    "purposes of energy recovery any fuel produced as provided in paragraph (1) or any fuel which "
   137	    "otherwise contains used oil or any hazardous waste identified or listed under section 6921 "
   138	    "of this title; and (3) any person who distributes or markets any fuel which is produced as "
   139	    "provided in paragraph (1) or any fuel which otherwise contains used oil or any hazardous "
   140	    "waste identified or listed under section 6921 of this title 1 shall file with the "
   141	    "Administrator (and with the State in the case of a State with an authorized hazardous waste "
   142	    "program) a notification stating the location and general description of the facility, "
   143	    "together with a description of the identified or listed hazardous waste involved and, in the "
   144	    "case of a facility referred to in paragraph (1) or (2), a description of the production or "
   145	    "energy recovery activity carried out at the facility and such other information as the "
   146	    "Administrator deems necessary. For purposes of the preceding provisions, the term \"hazardous "
   147	    "waste listed under section 6921 of this title\" also includes any commercial chemical product "
   148	    "which is listed under section 6921 of this title and which, in lieu of its original intended "
   149	    "use, is (i) produced for use as (or as a component of) a fuel, (ii) distributed for use as a "
   150	    "fuel, or (iii) burned as a fuel. Notification shall not be required under the second "
   151	    "sentence of this subsection in the case of facilities (such as residential boilers) where "
   152	    "the Administrator determines that such notification is not necessary in order for the "
   153	    "Administrator to obtain sufficient information respecting current practices of facilities "
   154	    "using hazardous waste for energy recovery. Nothing in this subsection shall be construed to "
   155	    "affect or impair the provisions of section 6921(b)(3) of this title. Nothing in this "
   156	    "subsection shall affect regulatory determinations under section 6935 of this title. In "
   157	    "revising any regulation under section 6921 of this title identifying additional "
   158	    "characteristics of hazardous waste or listing any additional substance as hazardous waste "
   159	    "subject to this subchapter, the Administrator may require any person referred to in the "
   160	    "preceding provisions to file with the Administrator (or with States having authorized "
   161	    "hazardous waste permit programs under section 6926 of this title) the notification described "
   162	    "in the preceding provisions. Not more than one such notification shall be required to be "
   163	    "filed with respect to the same substance. No identified or listed hazardous waste subject to "
   164	    "this subchapter may be transported, treated, stored, or disposed of unless notification has "
   165	    "been given as required under this subsection. (b) Effective date of regulation The "
   166	    "regulations under this subchapter respecting requirements applicable to the generation, "
   167	    "transportation, treatment, storage, or disposal of hazardous waste (including requirements "
   168	    "respecting permits for such treatment, storage, or disposal) shall take effect on the date "
   169	    "six months after the date of promulgation thereof (or six months after the date of revision "
   170	    "in the case of any regulation which is revised after the date required for promulgation "
   171	    "thereof). At the time a regulation is promulgated, the Administrator may provide for a "
   172	    "shorter period prior to the effective date, or an immediate effective date for: (1) a "
